Get ready to shake those wiggles out kiddos and join ME, Mrs. Meuret, for a MORNING MOVEMENT BREAK💪🏻 Families, I am SO EXCITED to start a virtual “brain break” for students at home and for parents, take this “brain break” as a time to relax. We may do @gonoodle, a fun fitness circuit, stretch, or just have a DANCE PARTY! My goal is to inspire kids to get up and MOVE! During this health epidemic, it is SO important to focus on our health and be mindful. So families, join me THIS FRIDAY at 11:00 am LIVE on Facebook for a “brain break!” Plus, it’s my B-DAY (WHOOT WHOOT) so there may be a birthday song or two for celebrating!🎉 Please feel free to share and spread the word. I can't thank everyone enough for all the help running the district tournament. The only person I will individually name is my wife. She planned and lined up help for weeks. She did an outstanding job.

Every wrestler that we put on the mat gave great effort in every match. Crowd was great, accommodations were fantastic, several great matches, things went well.

I had several people tell me that this was one of the best run districts that they have been to over the years. It takes a lot of people to make that happen.

Thanks Plainview,
Coach Boyer
